Carrier path: Data Analyst

Must-Have Skillset:

Technical:
SQL: For database querying and data manipulation.
Excel/Google Sheets: For basic data handling and initial analysis.
Python or R: For statistical analysis and more complex tasks (with relevant libraries like Pandas, NumPy, scikit-learn in Python; base R and tidyverse).
Data Visualization Tools: (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, Matplotlib, Seaborn) for creating clear reports.
Analytical:
Critical Thinking: To ask the right questions and interpret data.
Problem-Solving: To break down issues and find data-driven solutions.
Statistical Fundamentals: Understanding core statistical concepts.
Soft Skills:
Communication: Clearly explaining findings to technical and non-technical audiences.
Business Acumen: Understanding how data relates to business goals.
Good to Have:

Cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP)
Big Data tools (Hadoop, Spark)
Basic Machine Learning concepts
